Bill Spriggs, a renowned economist, has passed away, leaving behind a legacy of brilliance and inspiration. He challenged assumptions about racial discrimination, pay equity, and worker empowerment in labor markets. As the Economics Department Chair at Howard University and Chief Economist for the AFL-CIO, he tirelessly fought for economic justice, placing the voices and needs of workers at the forefront of policymaking. Bill's contributions extended to his roles in various economic policy positions in the federal government. Alongside his remarkable achievements, he will be remembered for his kindness, warmth, and humility.